26/11/2008
OSLO, Norway --Macedonia will open an embassy in Oslo in the first half of 2009, Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski announced on Tuesday (November 25th) during a meeting with Norwegian counterpart Jens Stoltenberg in the Norwegian capital. Currently, the Macedonian embassy in Sweden handles all Macedonian diplomatic and consulate relations with Norway. Norway, on the other hand, has had an embassy in Macedonia for ten years. Gruevski on Tuesday also met with King Harald V about Macedonia's development prospects and reforms, as well as difficulties in its efforts to join NATO. Gruevski and his delegation are working to drum up Norwegian investment in Macedonia. (MRT - 26/11/08; MIA - 25/11/08)
